ope, Asia, Africa, and Australia and adds new chapters on VAT avoidance and evasion and on China's VAT. Designed to illustrate, analyze, and explain the principal theoretical and operating features of value added taxes, including their adoption and implementation, this book will be an invaluable resource for tax practitioners and government officials"--</subfield><subfield code="c">Provided by publisher.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="596"><subfield code="a">44</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2="0" tag="650"><subfield code="a">Value-added tax</subfield><subfield code="x">Law and legislation.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2="0" tag="650"><subfield code="a">Spendings tax</subfield><subfield code="x">Law and legislation.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2="0" tag="650"><subfield code="a">Taxation of articles of consumption</subfield><subfield code="x">Law and legislation.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1="1" ind2=" " tag="700"><subfield code="a">Thuronyi, Victor</subfield><subfield code="e">author.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1="1" ind2=" " tag="700"><subfield code="a">Cui, Wei,</subfield><subfield code="d">1970-</subfield><subfield code="e">author.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1="4" ind2="0" tag="856"><subfield code="3">University of Alberta Access</subfield><subfield code="u">http://dx.doi.org/10.1017/CBO9781107337671</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="926"><subfield code="a">Internet Access</subfield><subfield code="w">LC</subfield><subfield code="c">1</subfield><subfield code="i">6804090-1001</subfield><subfield code="l">INTERNET</subfield><subfield code="m">UAINTERNET</subfield><subfield code="r">Y</subfield><subfield code="s">Y</subfield><subfield code="t">E-RESOURCE</subfield><subfield code="u">2/12/2015</subfield><subfield code="x">E-BOOK</subfield><subfield code="z">CBO</subfield></datafield></record>